textBeforeTable: At The Ursuline School: Captain of her high school team in 2009 … named Scholastic All-American in 2009 … four-time winner of the Scholar Athlete Award … two-time All-Section selection … three-time All-League selection … Ursuline team took first place in both the sectionals and the league all four years … team took first place at the Empire State Games in 2009. Personal: Daughter of Linda and Sean D’Arcy … father, Sean ’81CC, played football for Columbia … cousin Darcy Brown ’08CC rowed for Columbia … cousin Sean Darcy also attend Columbia (’09SEAS) … sister, Cara, rows for Boston College … cousin, Peter, rows for Iona College … member of the National Honor Society and the National Junior Honor Society … won the Laura Borton Scholarship for Leadership in 2009. 2010-11: Member of the 2011 ECAC squad, scoring points for Columbia in four different events … part of the 800 free relay that placed eighth … member of the 400 medley relay that finished 12th overall … qualified for the consolation finals of the 500 freestyle, finishing 14th overall in 5:05.25 … qualified for the consolation finals of the 200 freestyle, finishing 14th overall with a time of 1:55.16.  2012-13: Made her first Ivy League Championship squad, scoring points for the Lions in the 1000 free (21st) and the 200 free (16th), while also placing 29th in the 100 free. 2013-14: Capped the regualr season with a win the 500 free against Dartmouth with a time 4:59.30...
